           SHORT="decoding library used in akode_artsplugin in kdemultimedia"

cat << EOF
aKode is the decoding library used in akode_artsplugin in
kdemultimedia, and improves the aRts experience by fewer drop-outs,
more supported formats and fewer bugs in general.  It can also be used
directly without aRts in JuK and Amarok.

aKode supports decoding of MPEG audio, Ogg Vorbis, Ogg FLAC, old FLAC,
Speex, WAV, and Musepack audio.
EOF
